    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "3. Let $X$ and $Y$ be independent random variables, identically distributed according to the Normal distribution with mean 0 and variance 1, $N ( 0 , 1 )$ . ",
        "bbox": [
            191,
            136,
            801,
            187
        ],
        "page_idx": 1
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "(a) Find the joint probability density function of $( R , \\theta )$ , where ",
        "bbox": [
            221,
            189,
            766,
            206
        ],
        "page_idx": 1
    },
    {
        "type": "equation",
        "text": "$$\nR = (X ^ {2} + Y ^ {2}) ^ {1 / 2} \\quad \\text {a n d} \\quad \\theta = \\arctan (Y / X).\n$$",
        "text_format": "latex",
        "bbox": [
            305,
            210,
            687,
            231
        ],
        "page_idx": 1
    },
    {
        "type": "list",
        "sub_type": "text",
        "list_items": [
            "(b) Are $R$ and $\\theta$ independent? Why, or why not? ",
            "(c) Find a function $U$ of $R$ which has the uniform distribution on (0, 1), Unif(0, 1). ",
            "(d) Find a function $V$ of $\\theta$ which is distributed as Unif(0,1). ",
            "(e) Show how to transform two independent observations $U$ and $V$ from Unif(0,1) into two independent observations $X$ , $Y$ from $N ( 0 , 1 )$ . "
        ],
        "bbox": [
            221,
            234,
            801,
            351
        ],
        "page_idx": 1
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "4. Let $X$ be a random variable such that $E [ | X | ] < \\infty$ . Show that ",
        "bbox": [
            191,
            359,
            766,
            378
        ],
        "page_idx": 1
    },
    {
        "type": "equation",
        "text": "$$\nE [ | X - a | ] = \\inf  _ {x \\in R} E [ | X - x | ],\n$$",
        "text_format": "latex",
        "bbox": [
            371,
            381,
            623,
            406
        ],
        "page_idx": 1
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "if and only if $a$ is a median of $X$ ",
        "bbox": [
            191,
            409,
            482,
            426
        ],
        "page_idx": 1
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "5. Let $Y _ { 1 } , \\dots , Y _ { n }$ be iid observations from the distribution $f ( x - \\theta )$ , where $\\theta$ is unknown and $f ( \\mathbf { \\theta } )$ is probability density function symmetric about zero. ",
        "bbox": [
            191,
            434,
            801,
            483
        ],
        "page_idx": 1
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Suppose a priori that $\\theta$ has the improper prior $\\theta \\sim$ Lebesgue (flat) on $( - \\infty , \\infty )$ . Write down the posterior distribution of $\\theta$ . ",
        "bbox": [
            191,
            483,
            801,
            517
        ],
        "page_idx": 1
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Provides some arguments to show that this flat prior is noninformative. ",
        "bbox": [
            191,
            518,
            801,
            549
        ],
        "page_idx": 1
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Show that with the posterior distribution in (a), a 95% probability interval is also a 95% confidence interval. ",
        "bbox": [
            191,
            550,
            801,
            583
        ],
        "page_idx": 1
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "6. Suppose we have two independent random samples {Y1, $i = 1 , \\ldots , n \\}$ from Poisson with (unknown) mean $\\lambda _ { 1 }$ and $\\{ Y _ { i } , \\ i = n + 1 , \\dots , 2 n \\}$ from Poisson with (unknown) mean $\\lambda _ { 2 }$ Let $\\theta = \\lambda _ { 1 } / ( \\lambda _ { 1 } + \\lambda _ { 2 } )$ . ",
        "bbox": [
